urrected horse are Miss Lindstrom and the fried potatoes and Mr. O’Neil and the seductive client—and to give these people a voice. Adding new dimensions to the study of charity and social work, this book is essential to understanding and tackling poverty in the twenty-first century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPoorxServices forxAustralia. 0aPoorxServices forxEngland. 0aPoorxServices forxUnited States. 0aPoorxServices forzAustralia. 0aPoorxServices forzEngland. 0aPoorxServices forzUnited States. 0aSocial case workxAustralia. 0aSocial case workxEngland. 0aSocial case workxUnited States. 0aSocial case workzAustralia. 0aSocial case workzEngland. 0aSocial case workzUnited States. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311063872108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022665363140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226653662423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226653662/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-063872-1  DG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles